Nothing crazy as usual, only this time I'm starting to get morning wood which is great. (It's not) but aside from that I've been giving some though about me winning or losing this thing.

Been seeing a lot of people disparaging people for doing NNN and telling them to give up and that it's a stupid challenge which actively harms you, and your a moron for doing it.

Seeing stuff like that kinda got me going and reminded me why I'm doing this challenge, it's doing something that most people refuse to do because it's a daunting if not impossible challenge for some. I started this because I want to gain discipline and willpower which could help me later on in life, to prove to myself that I have the strength to not let my emotions control me, and also for the memes and it makes the days interesting.

But it's also given me an odd sense of clarity, on top of if I win, the satisfaction of proving people wrong and doing something everyone else refuses to do will be kinda nice. Won't make me better then anybody but it's a challenge that is about conquering ones own self, which is a neat concept to me if I'm being honest.

Obviously this is just a meme and I'm taking it a bit far, but only for myself, not for others. This whole challenge is a meme, so it should be at a surface level, be taken as a meme and nothing more unless the individual wants to take it farther for themselves, not for others.

We shouldn't be shaming people for losing a silly internet challenge, instead we should motivate and have fun and laugh along the way while it goes on. It's a once a year challenge, we don't need to belittle people for doing it or losing.

That being said, we are all nearly 2 weeks in now, were starting to enter [absolute territory](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kFZKgf5WG0g). Good luck lads.
